Bluetongue [BTV], Turkey
------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 11 Dec 2017 from Dr Nihat Pakdil, Deputy Undersecretary of Ministry, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Food, Agriculture and Livestock, ANKARA, Turkey

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 6 Nov 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 8 Dec 2017
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 30 Dec 2015
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 16
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Kavsit, Cine, Aydin
Date of start of the outbreak: 6 Nov 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Goats / 26 / 11 / 11 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Goats / 42.31 / 42.31 / 100 / 42.31
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Introduction of new live animals; vectors
Epidemiological comments: The first clinical symptoms were seen on [6 Nov 2017]. The sample taken was sent to a laboratory. The outbreak has just been notified because it was newly typed.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; quarantine; disinfection; control of vectors; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak (s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type/ Species/ Test/ Test date/ Result
Etlik Veterinary Control Central Research Institute (National laboratory)/ Goats / real-time reverse transcriptase/polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 8 Dec 2017 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

